physical_examinations.relevant_findings: A 2 × 2 cm swelling was observed in the right medial calcaneal region. The overlying skin appeared normal, with no redness, warmth, or tenderness. A 3 × 3 mm opening was noted in the center of the swelling, through which black dot-like granules discharged upon pressure. The range of motion of the ankle joint was maintained.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: The swelling was noticed two years ago and has slowly increased in size, causing minor discomfort when wearing shoes. Four months before presentation, dark granular discharge began to appear from the swelling.
